# Cockpit — host-shipped (system-scope), not a quadlet.
# =============================================================================
# Why this snippet exists
# -----------------------
# The bootc image (sodimo/harness) ships cockpit.socket system-scope. The
# rootless cockpit.container quadlet that used to live in this repo was retired
# (sodimo/dotfiles#23) because it fought the host cockpit for port 9090 and
# the auth model is identical between the two paths anyway (PAM against
# /etc/shadow).
#
# Activation (system-scope, on the harness, one-time):
#
#   sudo systemctl enable --now cockpit.socket
#
# Cockpit then listens on [::]:9090. Verify with:
#
#   ss -tlnp | grep :9090
#   curl -k https://127.0.0.1:9090/   # 200 OK, login form
#
# Public path (post-cloudflared, post-CF-Access)
# ----------------------------------------------
# 1. cloudflared host unit forwards `cockpit.sodimo.eu` to 127.0.0.1:9090.
# 2. Caddy route `cockpit.caddy` proxies to host.containers.internal:9090.
# 3. CF Access policy gates the hostname against Google Workspace; only
#    `@sodimo.eu` identities reach the cockpit-ws login.
# 4. To trust the CF Access JWT/header instead of asking PAM again, edit the
#    host-side /etc/cockpit/cockpit.conf (NOT this file) with:
#
#      [WebService]
#      Origins = https://cockpit.sodimo.eu wss://cockpit.sodimo.eu
#      ProtocolHeader = X-Forwarded-Proto
#      AllowUnencrypted = true
#
#      [basic]
#      action = none
#
#    See https://cockpit-project.org/guide/latest/authentication for the
#    upstream-supported header pass-through shape.
#
# Why the sodimo OS user has no password
# --------------------------------------
# `sodimo` keeps NP (no-password) in /etc/shadow; SSH-key over Tailscale is the
# break-glass path. Cockpit web is intentionally unreachable until CF Access
# fronts it. See `midday-handoff-cockpit-no-passwordless-web.md` (2026-05-05).
